Subject: [PATCH 5/5] =?UTF-8?q?T-Display=20P4:=20never=20cancel=20rollback?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20=E2=80=94=20keep=20the=20DualMesh=20launcher=20reachable?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The P4 framework libs bake in CONFIG_APP_ROLLBACK_ENABLE, so initArduino()
marks the slot valid on first boot and permanently captures the boot path:
every subsequent reset goes straight into headless Meshtastic and the
factory launcher (with its splash/slot picker) is unreachable. Override the
weak verifyRollbackLater() hook to defer verification forever — the
launcher boots this slot one-shot and every reset returns to the launcher,
same contract MeshOS follows.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.cpp | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.cpp b/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.cpp
index 9ee1b687e..c4a1cf730 100644
--- a/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.cpp
+++ b/variants/esp32p4/t-display-p4/variant.cpp
@@ -11,6 +11,18 @@
 
 extern esp_io_expander_handle_t io_expander;
 
+// DualMesh GRUB mode: the launcher boots this slot one-shot (PENDING_VERIFY)
+// so the NEXT reset falls back to the factory launcher. The Arduino core's
+// initArduino() would otherwise call esp_ota_mark_app_valid_cancel_rollback()
+// (CONFIG_APP_ROLLBACK_ENABLE is baked into the P4 framework libs), which
+// permanently captures the boot path — the device then resets straight into
+// headless Meshtastic and the launcher splash is unreachable. Returning true
+// here defers verification forever; we never mark ourselves valid.
+extern "C" bool verifyRollbackLater(void)
+{
+    return true;
+}
+
 extern "C" void initVariant(void)
 {
 #if defined(CONFIG_IDF_TARGET_ESP32P4) && defined(BOARD_SDMMC_POWER_PIN)
